1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,044
[Marcus] <i>This is the bullet casing</i>
<i>I retrieved.</i>

2
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:05,880
<i>Another group really did start the chaos</i>
<i>on the island that night.</i>

3
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:07,048
<i>Datu Rahman is innocent.</i>

4
00:00:07,132 --> 00:00:09,426
<i>Someone planted the intel we received.</i>

5
00:00:09,509 --> 00:00:12,303
<i>He's the one who fed us</i>
<i>false intel about Datu Rahman.</i>

6
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:13,763
<i>That's also why he was killed.</i>

7
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,349
<i>Straight from the mouth</i>
<i>of the high-ranking smuggler</i>

8
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,892
<i>I fought on the island.</i>

9
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:20,854
<i>Their protector is someone</i>
<i>inside the NLEA.</i>

10
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:22,939
There's a rat inside our own ranks.

11
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:24,816
[Marcus] <i>There's something else</i>
<i>you should know, sir.</i>

12
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:26,359
<i>I was the one who took Datu Rahman</i>

13
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:28,361
- <i>from the Zylverix building.</i>
- Where is he now?!

14
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:30,363
[Marcus] <i>The people who kidnapped him</i>
<i>tracked him down.</i>

15
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:33,324
<i>But his son managed to save him.</i>

16
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:35,535
[Azuelo] Give me one good reason

17
00:00:35,618 --> 00:00:39,581
why I shouldn't suspend you right now!

18
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:42,375
[Marcus] <i>I'm your only ally</i>
<i>if you want to solve this case.</i>

19
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:44,627
[Felix] I've already identified
Datu Rahman's son.

20
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,171
[Felix] <i>Jalil Abubakar.</i>

21
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:49,299
<i>I had my people check on him.</i>
<i>He's a member of the CDSU.</i>

22
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,675
I checked his files.

23
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:53,011
[Felix] <i>I couldn't find anything.</i>
<i>Nothing came up.</i>

24
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:54,262
Looks like everything was erased.

25
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:56,473
- We need to find this.
- [in English] Definitely, madam.

26
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:58,558
[Manalo] <i>These are serious accusations.</i>

27
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:01,227
[Dionisio] <i>You're going to make</i>
<i>a lot of enemies</i>

28
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:03,188
<i>with what you're saying.</i>

29
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:05,774
I don't care!

30
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,484
I'll make sure

31
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:12,489
the SID and the NLEA
are clean before I leave!

32
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:27,212
‪[mysterious theme music playing]

33
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,777
Usman.

34
00:01:53,947 --> 00:02:00,370
[gentle music playing]

35
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:03,957
[In Arabic] Peace be upon you.

36
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,376
- [in Arabic] Peace be upon you too.
- How are you?

37
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:09,129
I heard you spoke with Sir Mustapha?

38
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,554
I can't lie to Marcus.

39
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:19,472
Why don't we just tell him the truth?

40
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:20,640
Besides, you both want the same thing.

41
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:22,892
He's not part of this mission.

42
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:28,439
Marcus can be trusted.

43
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,608
He could help you too.

44
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:32,152
Why, Usman, do you think

45
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:34,946
Marcus tells you everything he's doing?

46
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,991
[sighs] Even so,
I still shouldn't be lying to him.

47
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:39,325
[Jalil] You're not lying to him.

48
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:42,370
You're just not telling him
everything you know.

49
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:43,288
‪[pensive music playing]

50
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:48,918
That's the same thing.

51
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,713
Usman, he's not part of this mission.

52
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,173
Yes, maybe he isn't corrupt.

53
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:56,676
Maybe he isn't working with the people

54
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,094
who destroyed our island.

55
00:02:58,177 --> 00:03:00,930
But those people
already manipulated him before.

56
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:05,059
So I hope you understand
why I can't trust him.

57
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:09,480
[pensive music continues]

58
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:24,537
Which one of them do you think
is hiding something?

59
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:30,835
[dramatic sting]

60
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,337
‪-[tense music playing]
‪-[sighs]

61
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:35,423
What I saw earlier isn't enough yet, sir.

62
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:39,552
But we already have a lead
on who the primary target is.

63
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,554
General Manalo, sir.

64
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:45,516
His eyes kept shifting around.

65
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,393
He couldn't look us straight in the eye.

66
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:04,702
Colonel Dionisio.

67
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,289
He was way too defensive.

68
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,083
What are you saying?

69
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,335
That there's a traitor in this agency?

70
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,754
You're going to make a lot of enemies

71
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:17,131
with what you're saying.

72
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:18,800
The two of you!

73
00:04:18,883 --> 00:04:23,721
[tense music continues]

74
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:26,015
[knock on door]

75
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:29,477
Sir.

76
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,728
Sir, look at this.

77
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,736
[In Arabic] <i>Peace be upon you.</i>

78
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:44,033
[tense music continues]

79
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,705
[Datu Rahman] <i>I am Rahman Abubakar.</i>

80
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:54,919
<i>The accusations against me are false.</i>

81
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:59,882
<i>That I'm allegedly selling</i>
<i>illegal firearms.</i>

82
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:10,310
[Datu Rahman] <i>Those weapons</i>
<i>were being dropped</i>

83
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:12,645
<i>into the sea near our island.</i>

84
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,441
<i>We hid them</i>

85
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:23,865
<i>to stop criminals</i>
<i>from smuggling those weapons.</i>

86
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:29,162
<i>It's also not true that I killed</i>

87
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:31,914
<i>the two police officers on patrol.</i>

88
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,960
<i>At that time,</i>

89
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:42,258
<i>I was being held captive</i>
<i>by unidentified men.</i>

90
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:48,681
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes,</i>

91
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:54,520
<i>take a closer look</i>
<i>at the people around you.</i>

92
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:59,067
<i>The people responsible for this</i>

93
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,944
<i>may be inside the NLEA itself.</i>

94
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:11,454
[tense music continues]

95
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:36,229
[brooding music playing]

96
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,665
[in English] Sit down, gentlemen.

97
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:04,882
[brooding music continues]

98
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:20,398
- [in English] Goddammit!
- [tense music playing]

99
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:23,776
Why did Datu Rahman
release a video like this?

100
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:27,238
[door clicks open]

101
00:07:27,321 --> 00:07:31,159
[Lara] Sir, Marcus,
Datu Rahman is provoking us.

102
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:32,660
He's tarnishing the NLEA and SID.

103
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:34,620
We need to find him immediately.

104
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:37,081
I don't think that's what he's doing.

105
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,125
Huh?

106
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:42,044
I think Datu Rahman is telling the truth.

107
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,966
You believe him?

108
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:52,805
Sir?

109
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,268
Sir?

110
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:05,610
[in English] I agree
with Agent Reyes, Agent Angeles.

111
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:09,780
[tense music playing]

112
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:34,055
[in English] Everything's working
according to plan, gentlemen.

113
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:38,809
Illegal firearms are flooding
the entire country.

114
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:44,190
Especially here in Metro Manila.

115
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:49,529
This upcoming deal
with the Japanese investors

116
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,280
must fail.

117
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:56,369
The people can't be given hope,
especially not now.

118
00:08:56,452 --> 00:09:00,498
[in English] We are approaching
a critical mass, gentlemen.

119
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:04,544
As crime keeps getting worse and worse,

120
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:08,297
the people are slowly
being consumed by fear,

121
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:12,885
which makes them lose trust
in the government even more.

122
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,429
[in English] That means…

123
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:20,476
our destabilization plan is thriving.

124
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:26,190
Power will soon be ours.

125
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:27,525
‪[dramatic music playing]

126
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:33,823
[in English] Together, we shall dismantle
this broken system

127
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:36,742
and build a better Philippines

128
00:09:37,451 --> 00:09:40,955
and a stronger republic!

129
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,625
For the republic!

130
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,712
- For the republic!
- For the republic!

131
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:08,733
[pensive music playing]

132
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:12,069
Are you sure that Datu Rahman
won't throw you under the bus?

133
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:16,741
Even if your intentions are pure,

134
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,743
what you did is still illegal detention.

135
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:22,079
You could still be terminated
from the service.

136
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,126
Sir, I think if he wanted to betray me,

137
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,669
he would've done it long ago.

138
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:32,506
He knows that I know he's innocent.

139
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,718
And he's challenging me to tell the truth.

140
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:40,890
Isn't that what we also want?

141
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:44,477
To flush those bastards out of their lair!

142
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:51,984
‪[music intensifies]

143
00:10:57,698 --> 00:10:59,283
[in English] We'll go ahead, sir.

144
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,868
[Manuel, in English] Go ahead.

145
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:06,999
[tense music playing]

146
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,841
- General.
- [Manuel] Yes?

147
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:18,344
Azuelo has finally put his trust in Reyes.

148
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:22,473
They now believe that someone
sabotaged Damai Island.

149
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:26,685
And that there are anomalies
occurring within the NLEA.

150
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:29,021
[Manuel] Don't let that get to you.

151
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,524
[in English] Azuelo is all bark.

152
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:33,442
He'll eventually stop.

153
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:35,778
What about Reyes, General?

154
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:37,738
He's a hard-headed one, as well.

155
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:40,074
He might even get in the way of our plans.

156
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:42,910
Just leave him be.

157
00:11:42,993 --> 00:11:44,161
[chuckles]

158
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:47,957
[in English] I have something
in mind for that man.

159
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:52,753
[ominous music playing]

160
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:54,088
[Manuel] For now,

161
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:57,216
let's focus on this.

162
00:11:57,299 --> 00:12:01,637
Taking down that Japanese investment deal.

163
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,901
[in English] Understood?

164
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,404
- [in English] Yes, sir!
- [in English] Yes, sir!

165
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,823
Sir, I'll head out first.

166
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,535
Colonel Solares.

167
00:12:28,456 --> 00:12:30,124
General.

168
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:31,959
You've got to see this.

169
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:38,674
[Datu Rahman] <i>Take a closer look</i>
<i>at the people around you.</i>

170
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:45,097
<i>The people responsible for this</i>

171
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,808
<i>may be inside the NLEA itself.</i>

172
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:51,395
- [thuds]
- [Manuel sighs deeply]

173
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:57,193
- [breathing heavily]
- [music intensifies]

174
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:06,410
- [intriguing music playing]
- [digital trilling]

175
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:13,459
- Where is it?
- [in English] Tracing IP address, ma'am.

176
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:18,297
- [digital trilling]
- [keyboard clacking]

177
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:28,474
[computer beeping]

178
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:38,651
[digital trilling]

179
00:13:38,734 --> 00:13:42,947
[intriguing music continues]

180
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:47,701
[computer beeps]

181
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:50,704
Ma'am. There's only vacant lot here.

182
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:52,373
[Buster] Based on data packets,

183
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:54,833
the signal came from a mobile hotspot

184
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:57,461
that was discarded
or turned off immediately.

185
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,880
The IP address is already inactive.

186
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:06,053
[intriguing music continues]

187
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:28,325
- [grunts, panting]
- Madam…

188
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,077
- [in English] Relax.
- [heavy breathing]

189
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,079
- [in English] Relax?!
- People will hear you.

190
00:14:32,162 --> 00:14:33,706
How can I relax, huh?!

191
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:35,624
[in English] I feel like
I'm losing control of everything!

192
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:39,086
[breathing heavily]

193
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:41,797
You let Marcus come back,

194
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:43,173
and you failed to keep an eye on him.

195
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:46,844
Felix, shut up! Shut up!
You're not helping!

196
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:49,638
What I hate most of all is losing control.

197
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:57,771
- [breathing heavily]
- [music intensifies]

198
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:04,486
‪[music concludes]

199
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:08,908
‪[tense music playing]

200
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:17,166
- Usman.
- What exactly are you planning?

201
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:19,710
Why did Datu Rahman release
a statement like that?

202
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:21,962
Jalil!

203
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:26,550
Usman, when we're here, call me Espina.

204
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:28,052
Fine.

205
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:29,637
But what's your plan?

206
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,556
I thought you wouldn't release
a statement like that.

207
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,184
I thought you were hiding it?
Why are you exposing it now?

208
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,769
Even Marcus is getting dragged!

209
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:38,437
I can't tell you all my plans!

210
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:41,231
You just have to trust me!

211
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,901
We know what we're doing.

212
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,372
‪-[door clicks shut]
‪-[tense unsettling music playing]

213
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:05,172
- You sent for me, sir?
- [Dionisio] Let's get down to business.

214
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:08,217
Why did Datu Rahman call you out?

215
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:11,845
Why does he say you know he's innocent?

216
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,263
Answer me.

217
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,557
Did he contact you?

218
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:19,061
[dramatic sting]

219
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:26,318
What's going on here?

220
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:28,237
Why didn't I know about this?

221
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,448
We just wanted to clear
something up with Agent Reyes

222
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:34,243
regarding the video Datu Rahman released.

223
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:37,496
[in English] You are
overstepping boundaries!

224
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:39,415
Reyes is under my command!

225
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:43,043
You can't question him without me!

226
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:47,756
Why? What would you like to know?

227
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:51,010
Why is he and Datu Rahman
saying the same thing?

228
00:16:52,302 --> 00:16:53,929
Are they working together?

229
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:54,847
‪[dramatic sting]

230
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:00,728
Sir, I don't know why Datu Rahman

231
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,604
mentioned my name in that video.

232
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:05,024
I have no control over his actions.

233
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:09,194
But that doesn't mean
what he's saying is wrong.

234
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:14,158
Do you really want to ruin
NLEA and SID's reputation?

235
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:17,578
Sir, the people behind
all of this nonsense,

236
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:19,997
those protecting the syndicates,

237
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:23,375
they're the ones destroying
the agency, not me.

238
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:27,337
If I find out that you're
working with Datu Rahman,

239
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:30,966
you won't just get a suspension, Reyes.

240
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,385
I'll personally put you in jail!

241
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:35,512
I'll do the same, sir.

242
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,307
Once I prove

243
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:41,435
that there are syndicate accomplices
in this room.

244
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:44,688
There's no such thing, Reyes!

245
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,231
[Marcus] How do you know that, sir?

246
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,734
Have you already done your investigation?

247
00:17:50,986 --> 00:17:53,447
[Marcus] You're only saying that
because of our badges.

248
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:57,785
But isn't that exactly what protectors do?

249
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:00,621
They hide behind badges.

250
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:06,043
‪[dramatic stinging]

251
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:09,755
You're all unbelievable.

252
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,091
You called him here,

253
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:14,093
asked him a bunch of questions,

254
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:17,638
but yet you refuse to listen
to him or let him speak!

255
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,271
[in English] Damn it. Let's go, Reyes.

256
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,108
[in English] Yes, sir.

257
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,861
[door clicks open]

258
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:46,792
[suspenseful music playing]

259
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:50,671
[sighs]

260
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:52,297
No one can know about this.

261
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,007
[sighs]

262
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:56,718
This plan must not fail.

263
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:01,515
[sighs]

264
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:16,446
[suspenseful music continues]

265
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,198
[in English] Neutralize the area.

266
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:20,117
There are no civilians there.

267
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,827
You're about to be ambushed!

268
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,501
[Dionisio, in English]
<i>Neutralize the area.</i>

269
00:19:29,585 --> 00:19:30,586
<i>There are no civilians there!</i>

270
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,379
- <i>You're about to be ambushed!</i>
- [radio static]

271
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:35,674
[Marcus] <i>This area is full of civilians.</i>

272
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:38,177
- <i>I repeat, this area is full of civilians!</i>
- [radio static]

273
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:43,849
[suspenseful music continues]

274
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:50,063
I can't end up like Del Mundo.

275
00:19:54,484 --> 00:19:55,736
- [gunshot]
- [thuds]

276
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:57,946
[suspenseful sting]

277
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:10,083
General Carillo's plan cannot be ruined.

278
00:20:11,418 --> 00:20:13,462
I do not care!

279
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,339
I'm retiring!

280
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:19,384
I'm going to make sure that SID

281
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:22,346
and NLEA is clean when I leave!

282
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,183
Screw you, Azuelo!

283
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:30,479
You dare try to act all high and mighty
now of all times?

284
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:32,898
You'll regret this.

285
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:40,614
[music intensifies]

286
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,256
[Marcus] Brother.

287
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,259
What's going on?

288
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,636
Why did you meet Espina?

289
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:06,848
Brother, I just verified something.

290
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:13,188
[inhales sharply] How are you?

291
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:16,525
I saw Datu Rahman's video.

292
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:19,194
- [sighs]
- [pensive music playing]

293
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:21,655
I'm fine, brother.

294
00:21:23,573 --> 00:21:25,909
We both know that what
he's saying is true.

295
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,621
I need your help.

296
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:32,582
Help? With what?

297
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,460
Brother, I know you know a lot of people

298
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:37,254
in the Muslim community.

299
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:41,383
We can use it to find
Jalil Abubakar's wherabouts.

300
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:48,640
[door clicks shut]

301
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:52,853
[tense music playing]

302
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:04,531
Brother, I'm sure people
are currently hunting

303
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:06,074
Datu Rahman and Jalil down.

304
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:08,118
They need to be safe.

305
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:11,872
I have to clean up the mess
we made on the island.

306
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:13,665
I have to protect them.

307
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:22,966
Alright, brother. I'll try.

308
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:25,260
But it won't be easy.

309
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,722
Because even if those
from the community know,

310
00:22:28,805 --> 00:22:30,599
they won't just simply reveal it.

311
00:22:31,183 --> 00:22:33,727
It is their priority
to protect Datu Rahman.

312
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:36,063
Especially now that they know
he's innocent.

313
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:38,690
Brother…

314
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:42,360
If the enemies get
to Datu Rahman and Jalil first,

315
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:45,030
their lives will certainly be in danger.

316
00:22:46,573 --> 00:22:49,034
I know I'm asking a lot from you,

317
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,619
but please just give it a try.

318
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:53,288
Brother, they can't die.

319
00:22:54,122 --> 00:22:58,126
A lot of secrets will be buried
should they perish.

320
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:09,137
[music intensifies]

321
00:23:11,765 --> 00:23:14,851
[Azuelo] Agent Marcus and I
share the same sentiments.

322
00:23:14,935 --> 00:23:19,272
Those syndicates are protected
by someone within our ranks!

323
00:23:19,356 --> 00:23:21,983
[Marcus] <i>Task Force Alpha</i>
<i>is at the forefront of this war.</i>

324
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:25,654
<i>So, if any of you</i>
<i>wants to back out, now's your chance.</i>

325
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:29,324
[man] <i>Will Datu Rahman surrender?</i>

326
00:23:29,407 --> 00:23:31,993
Will he make it out alive,
or will he be killed right away?

327
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:36,540
[Manuel] <i>What are you doing?</i>
[breathing heavily]

328
00:23:36,623 --> 00:23:37,874
[Lara, in English] <i>It's over for us!</i>

329
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:38,959
[Felix] <i>Jalil Abubakar.</i>

330
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:42,754
I'm hunting him down.

331
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:46,258
[Manuel] <i>Along</i>
<i>with his criminal of a father.</i>

332
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:49,052
<i>All of this is happening</i>
<i>because you lost Datu Rahman.</i>

333
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:52,639
[Marcus] <i>I'll do everything</i>
<i>to save your father.</i>

334
00:23:52,722 --> 00:23:55,392
<i>But the people behind this conspiracy</i>

335
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:57,727
<i>won't let you both survive.</i>

336
00:23:57,811 --> 00:24:00,063
<i>That's why you have to cooperate with me,</i>

337
00:24:00,147 --> 00:24:01,857
<i>Jalil Abubakar.</i>
